  <data name="CrawlText" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Gorgon

This is an example of the CORNEROFFSETS property available on the GORGONSPRITE object.

By setting the upper left, and upper right corner offsets we can skew the sprite to mimic the famous opening crawl from 
STAR WARS™
(©® Disney™ - [c#FFFF0000]Plz No Sue Kthxbye[/c]).

When the sprite is deformed, Gorgon will automatically correct the texture mapping so that the texture is perspective correct. This is what gives the text the faked 3D appearance that you're seeing now. This effect can be used to mimic many other types of pseudo 3D effects. For example, Mode 7 from the Super Nintendo.

You will also note that the text is fading out as it reaches the top. This is due to a property named CORNERCOLORS. This property allows sprites to set an independent color for each of the 4 corners of the sprite rectangle. In this case, we've set the alpha to 0 for the upper left and upper right corners.

That's all for now. This text will repeat itself.</value>
